replies.text:
@Bionic Man yoo i remember posting on one of tamers' vids that he should put featherine in sometime and it was just a joke (kinda) but i really actually do want to see WTC in tamers. more than being absolutely fucking bonkers to see, i genuinely do think WTC would fit perfectly in the tamers cinematic universe.

like rika would be entertaining as hell to watch in tamers' style. she's already depicted in the community as a substance-abusing doomer so imagine how hilarious she'd be if translated into tamers' language. on that note, i feel like erika furudo would basically look exactly like hatsune miku in tamers' artstyle so she'd fit in perfectly; i feel like she might be the most likely candidate to gain access to the underground crew based off that alone.

there's also the abundance of canon and implied same-sex and LGBTQ relationships in WTC that would be right up tamers' alley, imagine how far he could take it using light and L's relationship as a framework. lastly, i feel like WTC's aesthetic (especially ryukishi's artstyle) has that perfect niche, amateur, fringe anime quality to it that would fit fantastically with tamers' existing anime interests. it could easily fit into the legion of non-SU media he's into. not to mention that ryukishi's writing style lends itself surprisingly well to tamers' IMO, which is probably why the venn diagram of ryukishi and tamers fans looks like such a perfect circle (besides the fact that they're both incredibly niche groups of fans lmao)

so yeah in conclusion, i know its a total pipedream, especially with how long WTC as a series is; but part of me hopes to god that tamers eventually experiences WTC in some capacity or if he already has, just casually drops that shit on us in a vid. now that you got me thinking about the possibilities, it not only seems like a perfect fit but it would improve the cinematic universe tenfold (and hey, maybe 07th will get more readers out of it!) that'd be god-tier kino on top of the countless amount he's already produced. thank you for coming to my TED talk.
